HTTP-Server-Simple-Dispatched

Eases some of the pain of using HTTP::Server::Simple by providing a concise
and regular way to dispatch url requests (via regexes) and handlers that
receive HTTP::Response and HTTP::Request objects.  Please see the POD
documentation at Search CPAN for more details.

CAVEAT

This module is in a very early, unstable state.  Its API may change a whole
lot in subsequent releases!

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

CONTRIBUTING

The development branch lives at 
http://helios.tapodi.net/~pdriver/Bazaar/HTTP-Server-Simple-Dispatched/. 
Creating your own branch and sending me the URL is the preferred way to send 
patches.

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc HTTP::Server::Simple::Dispatched

Or at Search CPAN:

    http://search.cpan.org/dist/HTTP-Server-Simple-Dispatched

